</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/ecommerce-tips.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 28 Oct 2009 03:33:46 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Use Your Own Affiliate Program</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;"If you don't drive your business, you will be driven out of business." (B. C. Forbes)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A lot of people are
doing this mistake, they let themselves be driven out of business. How? By
starting a business and just hope that it will work. It’s the same with the
owners of e-commerce websites.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why do I say this?
Because most of them they are just presenting their products but they are not selling
 them.  As usual, you don’t have to reinvent the wheel, the solutions is in
front of you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easiest way to
increase your sites visibility and to “drive” visitors to your business is by
advertising. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Traditional online advertising
like CPC or CPM offers you the advantage of increasing your traffic, but not in
the best way. You will pay for clicks and for impressions but who knows what
you will receive. You just know for sure that you will pay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other way, is to
use your own affiliate program. You will pay, but you will pay only for sales,
not for impressions or clicks. In other words, pay less and receive more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why do you think big
players like amazon.com have their own affiliate programs? Because they know
how to drive their business. More affiliates, more sales, better business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The alternative? SEO, advertising,
and luck. Advertising can be expensive as we’ve discussed. Let’s think a little
about SEO. It’s good to be SEO optimized, but I don’t think you would like to
put all your chances on Google, Bing or Yahoo.  Everyone knows that having a
single source of visitors is risky, and you can
have a surprise in one morning when you wake up and they’ve changed their
algorithm.  If you are driving your business based on luck, you don’t have a
business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let’s talk a little
about affiliate’s advantages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From my experience as
a publisher and affiliate, I can say that I prefer to use affiliate programs
instead of advertising.  I think the biggest problem in using advertising is
that there is a store owner, and there is publisher as a third player. This
third player is usually the one who delivers the advertisement, e.g. Google
Adsense, AdBrite, Clicksor and others. From my point of view as a publisher, I
don’t like this because I don’t know exactly how much money the store owner is
paying for advertisement and how much money I receive and how much money the
third party receives.  From my point of view as affiliate, I like this because
I receive a fixed percent from the sales, so I know how much money I’ve
generated for the store owner and I know I was paid correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It’s in your power to
convince the owners of other websites about the advantages of becoming your
affiliate and to drive your business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;em&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ionut Lupu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Virtue Affiliate, &lt;a href="http://www.avaffiliate.com"&gt;www.avaffiliate.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/em&gt;
</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/use-your-own-affiliate-program.aspx</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 Dec 2009 04:32:22 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Reducing and Capitalizing on Shopping Cart Abandonment</title><description>&lt;p&gt;As e-tailers, we all know too 
well how many shopping cart abandonments happen on a day-to-day basis. 
Those are actual people who have put an item from our website in their 
cart as a sign and interest and BOOM…they disappear. To another website 
they go and perform the same task or actually purchase an item. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to an e-tailing group 
survey, “nearly 60% of U.S. online retailers experience cart abandonment 
rates of over 20%,” reports e-Marketer. A study by PayPal and comScore, 
“found 45% of US online shoppers had abandoned shopping carts multiple 
times in just three weeks. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most importantly from the merchants’ 
point of view, the average cost of abandoned goods in those shopping 
carts was $109. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the same study, 46% of online 
shoppers said high shipping charges were a ‘very important reason’ 
for emptying carts.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this particular study, other 
reasons for shopping cart abandonment were:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Wanted to comparison 
  shop: 37% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Lack of money: 36% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Wanted to look for 
  a coupon: 27% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Wanted to shop offline: 
  26% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Couldn’t find 
  preferred pay option: 24% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Item unavailable 
  at checkout: 23% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Couldn’t find 
  customer support: 22% &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Security concerns: 
  21% &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, how can we as merchants 
improve our shopping cart abandonment rates? First, you must use a platform 
in which the data allows for you to actually contact some of these shoppers 
and it all starts with them creating accounts on your website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a shopper creates an account 
on your website that means you have captured that shoppers data such 
as a name and a phone number or email. You can go through shopping cart 
abandonment data daily, or once every two days, see what shoppers with 
accounts have abandoned their cart and you can choose to email them 
or call them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The best results from this 
strategy I have personally seen have come from emailing or calling these 
customers and offering them a 5-10% coupon off their purchase.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, some tips from reasons 
stated by the research by PayPal and comScore are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Offer coupons: In 
  this economy, shoppers are really looking to spend as least as possible 
  and really looking for coupon codes online. &lt;/li&gt;

  &lt;li&gt;Phone number: Make 
  sure you have a phone number where customers can reach you. Often times 
  shoppers feel unsecured when they don’t see they can talk to a live 
  person and may move on right there and then.&lt;/li&gt;

  &lt;li&gt;Pay Options: Offer 
  as many payment options as possible. That includes all types of credit 
  cards, PayPal, Google Checkout, and Bill Me Later if you qualify.&lt;/li&gt;

  &lt;li&gt;Customer Support: 
  This can go hand in hand with the phone number issue but make LIVE CHAT 
  and a PHONE NUMBER prominent to the shopper. Make sure they know how 
  to contact you and make it readily available for them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pablo Palatnik heads the Marketing Department 
at Fortune3, a &lt;a href="http://www.fortune3.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Shopping Cart Software&lt;/a&gt; Company 
based out of Doral, Florida.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/reduce-shopping-cart-abandonment.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Aug 2009 07:20:09 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>How does Froogle help me sell more?</title><description>

You may have heard of &lt;a href="http://froogle.google.com/"&gt;Froogle&lt;/a&gt;, and if you haven't,you may have been missing out on sales. Froogle is a service offered by Google which is designed specifically to search shopping carts. It's a bit different from the normal Google search engine though. If you want to be listed in Froogle, you need to supply them information about your cart (more on that later). It's a cheap and easy way to do online shop promotion - and it's free!
&lt;P&gt;
People looking to buy a particular item can search for it in Froogle which will provide details about merchants selling that item and their price. For example, I recently heard about the "Fridge Phonics magnetic letter set" which I thought would be great for my young son. I went to Froogle, searched for it, found several shops selling it and bought it. If you sell that product but aren't listed on Froogle, you weren't even in the running. It's ecommerce marketing with minimal effort!
&lt;P&gt;
So how do you get your products listed in Froogle? Well, the first thing is that Froogle currently only works in the USA, UK and Germany. If you are outside those countries, sorry, you'll have to wait for Froogle to come to you. If you are in one of those countries, start by reading through the &lt;a href="https://www.google.com/froogle/merchants/"&gt;Froogle merchants guide&lt;/a&gt; to get some information. The good news is that some shopping carts are starting to automate Froogle feeds to make it painless. For example, &lt;a href="http://www.shopping-cart-reviews.com/carts/PDG-Shopping-Cart.aspx"&gt;PDG Shopping Cart&lt;/a&gt; will automate Froogle uploads for you.&lt;P&gt;

If you have a shopping cart which doesn't support Froogle and don't want to do it the hard way, not all is lost. There are several services which will help you get your products listed in Froogle, such as &lt;a href="http://froogle.somacon.com/"&gt;Somacon's Data Feed Service&lt;/a&gt;, albeit with a fee attached.


</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/Froogle.aspx</link><pubDate>Fri, 08 Jul 2005 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Creating Easy to Use Shopping Carts</title><description>Shopping cart abandonment – where a customer drops out part way through a 
purchase - is a common problem for merchants. Statistics show that most shopping 
cart abandonments happen because it was not user friendly enough for the 
customer. Customer usability is a must, and should be a large factor when you 
are determining which shopping cart is right for your business. You’ve probably 
been shopping yourself where you gave up in sheer frustration. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In most cases, the developer of the shopping cart system will have a demo 
shopping cart set up. Try out that demo, and view it from a customer's 
perspective, as well as an administrators perspective. A key feature to look for 
in terms of customer usability, is clear direction. Will the customer easily 
know what to do next? Once they add an item to the shopping cart, will they 
easily see the option to keep shopping, or to check out? Is searching for 
products easy? If possible, have someone who isn't computer savvy test the demo, 
and get their opinion of it. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

Your online shopping cart pages should be easy to navigate. If your customer 
can’t figure out how to get from one page to the next, you will lose them. 
Furthermore, the pages need to load quickly, so no large images or flash on your 
site. The ability to suggest cross sell or add-on products may increase sales as 
well as provide useful information to your customers. It may say something to 
the effect of "Customers who purchased product A, also purchased product B, C, 
and D."&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Your customer should not be required to have any special programs installed or 
turned on, such as flash or JavaScript. Some customers won't even understand 
what these things are, and requiring them makes your shopping cart unusable by 
many – statistics show as many as 10% of users don’t have these enabled. If a 
customer cannot figure out how to use your shopping cart, it won't matter how 
interactive or pretty it is.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Availability of products should be clearly noted, as soon as the product page 
loads. You will lose a customer for life if they go all the way through the 
shopping process, and the checkout process, only to discover that the product 
they wanted is unavailable, or that it must be back ordered. Also, each time 
your customer interacts with the shopping cart, they should be made aware that 
their action was noted. This will prevent the customer from performing the same 
action - over and over - in frustration.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Customers should know what their payment options will be before they start 
adding products to their cart. It’s frustrating to go through the selection 
process, only to get to the checkout and are not able to pay using the options 
listed. Make the options clear from the very beginning.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Finally, the actual checkout process must be user friendly. This is where the 
majority of the shopping cart abandonments occur. The checkout process should 
only be used to get the customers shipping information, and billing information. 
People don't like to share their information, and asking for too much 
information, along with billing information will most likely cost you sales.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
The more user friendly your shopping cart is, the more positive your customers 
shopping experience will be. If you made it a good experience, the customer will 
probably return to buy more from you in the future.&lt;br&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/shopping-cart-usability.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jun 2005 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Your Web host and your Shopping Carts: Friend or Foe?</title><description>When choosing shopping cart software, you will need to take your web host into 
consideration. You do not want to purchase shopping cart software until you know 
for sure that it is compatible with your web host servers, and that you will be 
able to set it up on the server. Making your purchase without having the proper 
information is not advised.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

Many webhosts offer free shopping carts. You should thoroughly check out the 
features to make sure it’s a suitable shopping cart – you often get what you pay 
for. You should note two things about using the shopping cart provided by your 
web host. First, if you need to change hosts, the shopping cart may not easily 
move with you. Second, in most cases, your web host will not offer support for 
the shopping cart. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
If you have decided that the shopping cart offered by your web host is not for 
you, your search is just beginning, and 
&lt;a href="http://www.ecommercespot.com"&gt;Ecommerce Spot&lt;/a&gt; can help 
you with that search. You will need to know several things about your web host 
while conducting your search, such as whether your website is hosted on a linux 
or windows server. Contact your web host to find out the information about the 
server. You should also ask about having SSL set up on your account, this is 
often required by the shopping cart. Sometimes there is an additional monthly 
fee for enabling SSL.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Find out what technology (ASP, PHP, CGI, ASP.NET, etc) are supported and which 
database (MySQL, SQL Server, Access, etc), and if applicable, what versions. 
Most shopping cart software will require at least one of each of these to be 
available. Armed with that list of technologies from your web host, you can use 
that to search on this site and make a short list.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Make sure that you want to use your current web host for your ecommerce 
activities before setting up your shopping cart. If they are not using the most 
up-to-date software for their dedicated servers and operating systems, you need to find a 
new host. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
By communicating with your web host during your shopping cart selection process, 
you will avoid many problems that could occur after your purchase. If your web 
host is uncommunicative, you should look for a new host. If they cannot 
communicate with you to help ensure that you purchase the right shopping cart 
software, they probably won't be very communicative when you run into website 
related problems later on.&lt;br&gt;


</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/shopping-cart-web-hosting.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jun 2005 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>nopCommerce Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;Creating and operating an eCommerce can be a challenging task. The market is over-populated with tons of commerce platform providers, making choosing the perfect fit for your business an overwhelming process. Well, also the cost of using the platform can add to your already stress. Today we will review one of the popular free, open-source platforms for creating an eCommerce website; That is nopCommerce.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;What is nopCommerce?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nopComemerce is a popular secure eCommerce platform; that is free to download. It's an open-source platform, making is scalable, flexible and customizable shopping cart as per individual needs. NopCommerce is an ASP. Net base with MS SQL 2008 or higher backend database. It has a robust management module to manage the store, product, customers, discount &amp; coupons, wish list, etc. nopCommerce is downloaded by more than 1.8 million times and host over 27 000 stores.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;nopCommerce Price&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nopCommerce is free to download eCommerce platform. The only cost you will encounter are for hosting, maintenance and for third party add-ons to expand your eCommerce functionality. The best hosting company for nopCommerce are Host4ASP.NET, WinHost, and Arvixe
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;nopCommerce ease-to-use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nopCommerce is a plug and play software, where you simply download the software and within a few clicks, you will be able to accept orders on your newly created eCommerce website. The admin looks clean, even though is a little overcrowded with information, you can easily find your way to customizing your store. As an open source shopping cart and if you are a developer/coder, nopCommerce allows you to scale completely and customizable to your specific needs. You can check out their demo store, and you will clearly see why people prefer nopCommerce against eCcommerce providers like WooCommerce.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;nopCommerce Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nopCommerc is built-in with a lot of out-of-box features that you will need to create and run an eCommerce platform successfully. I will brief you on some of the outstanding nopCommerce functions.&lt;br&gt;
With the nopCommerce platform, you have a fully functional mobile, responsive commerce website allowing your customers to purchase your products/services through any devices.
The multi-store feature of nopCommerce allows you to run multiple stores from one administration panel. It allows you to share data of catalogs between stores and customers can login in all stores using the same credentials.&lt;br&gt;
The multi-language feature expands your selling point to any part of the world. Your website will be available in many languages, allowing your customers to have a pleasant user experience on your site.&lt;br&gt;
nopCommerce has an excellent product management features that let you create product attributes, product comparison, inventory management, full control of product prices, sell downloadable products, ratings, and product reviews.&lt;br&gt;
For marketing your website, nopCommerce comes with built-in features to take your business to the next level. It offers features such as discount and coupons, reward point system, gift cards, social media marketing, etc. nopCommerce also allows access to manage customized URLs and keywords tags to boost your website ranking.&lt;br&gt;
NopCommerce integrated with the over 50 payment gateways that allow you to accept all major credit and debit cards. These include PayPal, Autorize.net, Google Checkout, SagePay, Stripe, Eway, etc.&lt;br&gt;
They also integrate with major shipping services such as USPS, UPS, FedEx, Australia Post, Canada Post, etc.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nopCommerce has an active forum, where you can find the answer to most of the issues regarding the shopping cart. You can contact them directly through the contact us page and send an email on your issue. They usually take 24 hours or so in response to your email. Additionally, you can use nopCommerce documentations, or you can pay for a premium support system for your website.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Will nopCommerce be a great platform for your business scenario?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a small to medium business then without doubt nopCommerce is a great tool for starting an online business. NopCommerce is free, open-source eCommerce platform with out-of-the-box feature rich system to operate an eCommerce website. Features such as multi-store, Multi-language and multi-currency will surely increase your sales in a minimum time frame.&lt;br&gt;
I would recommend this shopping cart for beginners and business that have a small budget plan for the eCommerce adventure.&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/nopCommerce-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Mon, 13 Feb 2017 09:09:27 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Intershop Commerce Suite Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;Intershop Commerce Suite is an eCommerce platform that is relatively easy to setup and start running an eCommerce business. The platform has been offering eCommerce solutions since 1994. Intershop Commerce Suite is flexible, scalable and customizable to suit any business model or organizational structure. Using this platform, you can market your brands, sell your products worldwide and implement strategies to grow your business. With Intershop Commerce Suite you can expect seamless Omni-channel shopping experience for your customers.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Intershop Commerce Suite eCommerce development models&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are three different development models available to use with the Intershop Commerce Suite. Some people prefer an easy all-in-one approach, and some would like to be involved in building their eCommerce store.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;1. Cloud&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
Intershop Commerce Suite Cloud is the fastest and easiest way to enter the eCommerce world. This solution offers the infrastructure and operates the platform as a SaaS (Software as a Service), giving you access to robust eCommerce technology functionality. The cloud base solutions offer benefits such as quick setup period, full, enterprise commerce functionality. Flexible scalability attractive pricing models, constant availability of new features, etc.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;2. Managed&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
The Managed solution offers maximum flexibility to your eCommerce website. Intershop Commerce Suite Managed allows to decide how you want to operate your eCommerce platform; either use your hosting, Intershop hosting services or a 3rd party host provider. You have the freedom to choose your in-house services and which to outsource to Intershop. The benefit for the Managed solutions includes flexible hosting and license options, optimum use of own IT services, custom mix of resources, infinite adaptability.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;3. Enterprise&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
The enterprise model offers unlimited freedom for you eCommerce solution. You will get maximum control of the platform enabling you to host your website in your data center and administered by your IT specialists. This model allows deep integration and detailed customization to meet your individual requirement for your business, plus retain total control of all your business-critical data. The benefits of using the Enterprise model include full platform control, universal adaptability, unlimited scalability on all business-relevant elements, deep customization, and integrations, optimum use of own IT resources.&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Intershop Commerce Suite Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The platform offers an all-in-one package approach that comprises of product information management, order management, web content management and personalized customer communications. Let looks at some Intershop Commerce Suite features in details;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Omni-Channel Management:&lt;/b&gt;enable you to manage all your channel, service, content, data, and integration with efficiency in a single system.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Experience Management:&lt;/b&gt;offers convenient features like search, filter and product configuration; that create an enjoyable shopping experience for customers. Other functions include personalized marketing campaigns like product recommendation and product advice that open new possibilities for a one-on-one approach.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Product Information:&lt;/b&gt;gather and manage product data, ensure optimum data quality and share your product data on all devices.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Customer Management:&lt;/b&gt;easily collect and manage data generated when interacting with clients and use them to boost performance like marketing campaigns, personalize communication with its customers.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Transaction Management:&lt;/b&gt;use popular payment gateways and shipping methods to receive payment and ship out customers orders.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Organization Management:&lt;/b&gt;manages users their role and rights access to the platform. You can also easily manage your international business sales and adapt flexibly to local demands.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Analytics &amp; Report:&lt;/b&gt;keep a close watch on your key business parameters that affect business performance with web analytical tools, dashboard ad widgets, reports, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Operational Excellence:&lt;/b&gt;high-security architecture, performance, and scaling infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt; &lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Intershop Commerce Suite Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intershop offers both phone and email support each tailored to a particular region Europe and America. Intershop support agreement provides three types of Support Agreement for purchases namely; Maintenance Support, Maintenance Support Plus, and Partner Support. You can also get useful information, using Intershop knowledge base, documentations or perhaps use the ticket support system.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Intershop Commerce Suite Bottom Line&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intershop is an Omni-channel eCommerce solution that has a good track record in the eCommerce market for many years. Throughout its establishment, the platform has been evolving to meet the demand of the eCommerce world. It offers out-of-the-box eCommerce development models that are flexible and affordable to both small to large enterprises.
I would recommend Intershop to a business that wants an eCommerce platform which goes an extra mile to provide individual services which help business to market and sell their product efficiently.
&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/Intershop-Commerce-Suite-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 27 Oct 2016 11:12:26 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>CoreCommerce Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;CoreCommerce is an eCommerce solution that enables you to create and maintain an online site easily. It is a web-hosted platform, which means you will only need a secured internet connection and web browsers to use the platform. The hosting is outsourced to Rackspace this means you will not need to worry about security and maintenance. During its inception, CoreCommerce has over 13 000 businesses and in an area of over 70 countries has created online stores with the platform. CoreCommerce allows you to add and maintain products, order, and customers smoothly.&lt;br&gt;
The platform does have its benefits and limitations, continue reading as we analysis what you can expect if you choose CoreCommerce as your business partner.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Pricing&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CoreCommerce has a good starting price point for both small to large enterprises. They provide a 15-days free trial period, which does not require you to make any commitments. There are five plans for CoreCommerce both with specific benefits and limitations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Pioneer Plan $40/month - include 300 product listings, 5 email accounts, 4GB bandwidth and 1GB of storage;&lt;br&gt;
2. Advanced Plan $90/month - include 2000 product listings, ten email accounts, unlimited bandwidth and 5GB of storage;&lt;br&gt;
3. Professional Plan $140/month - include 6000 product listings, 15 email accounts, unlimited bandwidth and 10GB of storage;&lt;br&gt;
4. Premier Plan $200/month - include unlimited product listing, 25 email accounts, unlimited bandwidth and 50GB storage;&lt;br&gt;
5. Enterprise Plan $600/month - include unlimited products, email account, bandwidth, and storage space.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
There are no transaction fees when signing up for CoreCommerce but should you sign up for cheaper plans you can expect an increase in your expenses for bandwidth overcharges and extra storage space. Each additional 1GB of bandwidth cost $9.00 and $9.00 for every 100MB over your monthly plan. The are no additional fees for changing from one CoreCommerce plan to another, but it is advisable to choose wisely as you might waste a lot of money on cheaper plans.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ease of Use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the appearance, the backend admin panel can seem overwhelming for the user not familiar with interfaces like WordPress, but with time you will be able to navigate and customize your storefront flawlessly.&lt;br&gt;
The CoreCommerce setup wizard is very simple to use, with access to the five top store setting component; design, product management, payment options, tax setting, and shipping settings.
The dashboard of CoreCommerce is customizable, allowing you access to choose what analytical data you would like to appear on the dashboard such as revenue graph, RSS feeds, Order abandonment, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CoreCommerce offers an extensive list of out-of-the-box eCommerce features for all their monthly plans that every eCommerce business needs to succeed. The platform is built in with Point of Sale (POS), auto-calculated taxes, one-page checkout, phone order system, shipping method options, etc.&lt;br&gt;
For your website design CoreCommerce offer more than free themes and buttons, a variety of product details templates pages, built-in, content management, ability to upload a logo, drag and drop design element without the need of knowing coding.&lt;br&gt;
You can also increase your website search ranking by using CoreCommerce SEO features such as clean products, content pages URLs, auto-generated meta tags, custom tags and you can set page titles individually,&lt;br&gt;
CoreCommerce shipping features include major shippers like USPS, UPS, FedEx, DHL, Australia Post and Canada Post and the ability to print labels for them; multiple shipping addresses, live shipping rates, etc.&lt;br&gt;
You will be able to receive credit card payment with PayPal, Google Checkout, COD, Checkout by Amazon, etc. Furthermore, you can increase your payment option with more than 25 payment gateways.&lt;br&gt;
CoreCommerce also provides addition integrations and add-ons to enhance your eCommerce experience under "Plugin Settings" in the backend store settings. From here you will find an extensive list of extensions which includes social commerce, constant contact's, Google Analytics, interest, eBay, etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CoreCommerce has a good reputation for providing quality customers services with their support department based in the USA. You can get help via live chat, phone, and email at no additional cost for 24 hours a day.&lt;br&gt;
Other support systems are a knowledge base, video tutorials, monthly webinars and also can find them on Facebook and Twitter.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CoreCommerce offers eCommerce solutions on affordable price tags both for small to large enterprises. Their customer services are exceptional of which every eCommerce business needs to run their business successfully, plus all CoreCommerce plans come with equal access to the platform features. CoreCommerce is a secure hosting solution, flexible and customizable at the same time to your individual need.&lt;br&gt;
I would recommend CoreCommerce to a business that does not expect lots of data transfer and want to sell online without worrying about security and customers' data quicker. The platform offers a 15-day trial period without commitment, be sure to utilize it before making your choice.&lt;p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/CoreCommerce-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 27 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>WooCommerce Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;We all know the struggle one goes through to choose an eCommerce platform for online business. There is hundreds of platform in the market, both free or paid, open-source or hosted and eCommerce website builder or simply a plugin you can add to your existing website. One needs to make sure he/she is choosing the perfect fit as the business success highly depends on your choice. If you are having a website on the WordPress content management system and would like to transform it into an eCommerce business than WooCommerce is an ideal plugin solution. Read further as we provide insight on the most popular eCommerce plugin for WordPress.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;What exactly is WooCommerce?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WooCommerce is the most popular eCommerce platform choice for many businesses and its a plugin for WordPress content management system. It's open-source eCommerce solution that is free to download and installs. It can be used on any WordPress websites and blogs or use to create an eCommerce website using WordPress. WooCommerce is a complete, flexible, scalable and customizable plugin, so can create your online store that looks and works exactly as per your requirements. WooCommerce is a great eCommerce solution for both small and large enterprises.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Pricing&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The WooCommerce is free to download for your WordPress website eCommerce solution. They do not charge transaction fees nor bandwidth or storage fees.&lt;br&gt;
However, that does not WooCommerce is free of all the expenses. You will need to purchase hosting plan (preferable Bluehost), security and various of add-ons and extensions to increase your eCommerce experience. These range from free to hundreds of dollars.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Ease to Use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WooCommerce was built to easily integrate with WordPress, making it an ideal eCommerce choice for millions of WordPress users. You can quickly install the plugin on the WordPress website using the "Add New" option in the Add-ons feature tab. Since it's an open-source plugin, you have unlimited scalability and customizable option along with access to HTML and CSS.
Right from the start of the installation, you will be helped by a 5-minute setup wizard that walks you through the basic steps to getting started. You can flawlessly add products, configure store payment gateway and shopping methods.&lt;br&gt;
Well, if you are already familiar with WordPress then I believe you will not have any problem to navigate WooCommerce plug-in.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WooCommerce offers tons of out-of-the-box features that are needed to run an eCommerce business. You can have unlimited product and category listings, product management, order management inventory tracking and much more. WooCommerce also offers responsive website design which gives an opportunity for your storefront and admin panel responsive on many devices on the go. Other noticeable features are such as collections support, shipping calculator on the checkout, discounts, and coupons, guest checkout and one-page checkout, product reviews, etc. Because WooCommerce is an open-source platform, there is a community of developers who work together to make sure that the plugin remain free and all eCommerce features are available. You can also benefit from 300+ free add-ons and hundreds of tons of paid extensions.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Web Design&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even though WooCommerce is easily integrated into a WordPress theme, it is recommended to use WooThemes for your website. This is because only by using Woo product you are eligible for WooCommerce web ticket support. You can choose from a vast collection of WooCommerce themes both free and paid option available in the range of $40 to $140. And as mentioned, earlier, WooCommerce offers a responsive design that a compatible with all devices. If you are a non-technical person than you can customize color changes, banners, content, taglines and header images. For a more advanced person, the system offers more control over the appearance of your store with HTML and CSS stylesheet. Since WooCommerce is open-source, there no limits to customization.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Payment Gateways and Shipping Methods&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WooCommerce comes with five built-in payment gateways that include Direct Bank Transfer, Cash on Delivery, Cheque Payments, PayPal and Simplify Commerce. You can also integrate other most popular gateways like Authorize.Net, PayFast, Stripe, Amazon Payments, FirstData, etc.&lt;br&gt;
You may also add an extension to the shipping method that includes using USPS, UPS, FedEx and much more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;WooCommerce Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many open-source shopping carts have floppy customers services, and WooCommerce is not an exception as it also comes with limited personal support. Other shopping carts like Shopping Cart Elite, Magento, etc., offers many different types of support like email, live chat or phone, but for WooCommerce you will only be able to submit a web ticket. Remember this is support is limited to those you use WooThemes templates for their websites.&lt;br&gt;
However, as an open-source cart, there is a large community of user to help you. You can also access WooCommerce documentation, Knowledge Base, Video Tutorials and the community forum.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For those that are using the WordPress content management system, WooCommerce is an ideal plugin to transform your already popular website into an eCommerce business. Not only is it free, but also an open source platform, giving you greater advantages to your eCommerce site with flexibility and unlimited customizability. It is easy, friendly and scalable to both small to large business enterprises.
&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/WooCommerce-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 27 Oct 2016 09:13:08 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>VirtueMart Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;We all know the importance of choosing the right eCommerce platform for our online business. The success of an eCommerce business lies in selecting the right and eCommerce platform to build an online store. This depends on the price, features, level of customization, support and many factors involved in creating an online store.&lt;br&gt;
There are hundreds of eCommerce platforms and even CMS that can be transformed into an eCommerce website using dedicated eCommerce plug-in. If you are hosting your site using the Joomla content management system and want to convert your site into an eCommerce store, then look no farther than VirtueMart Plugin. Continue reading as we uncover this eCommerce plugin as your eCommerce solution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;What is VirtueMart?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VirtueMart is open-source eCommerce plugin for Joomla content management system. It is slightly different from other shopping carts like Shopify or Big Cartel as it works in conjunction with Joomla. This means it only works on a website that is hosted on Joomla CMS. VirtueMart is a free PHP eCommerce solution which is flexible and customizable to individual need.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Pricing&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As noted above, VirtueMart is free, open-source plug-in to download for Joomla but you will need a budget some expenses for operating your online store. This expenses cost will include hosting, security, merchant accounts for order process with a credit card and developer/designer (see why below).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ease of Use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VirtueMart is relatively easy to use once, flexible and scalable. The new version of VirtueMart user interface is intuitive, the setting buttons are visible and displayed clear from high priority to low. However, if you are not a tech-oriented person, you will need a developer/design to the initial installations and dig deep into the source code to create a unique store for your online business. The new version of VirtueMart version 3.0.18 is compatible with both Joomla 2.5 and Joomla 3.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VirtueMart offers an unlimited number of product and category listings. The plug-in provides many out-of-the-box features which include order tracking, various prices and currency, custom attributes, coupon codes, product reviews and ratings, guest checkout, product display (latest, top ten sales, newest, featured, etc.), multilingual, etc.&lt;br&gt;
To receive payment on your VirtueMart store, you will need to use signup for a merchant account. Payment gateways that are included in the system include PayPal, Amazon, Skrill, Authorize.net, cash on delivery, etc. And since it's a PCI compliant, your customers can use the credit card at peace knowing that their data will be kept safe.&lt;br&gt;
VirtueMart offers many third-party extensions of many are heavily priced. But since its plugin for Joomla, you can benefit with 8000 Joomla extensions to increase your website experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open-source software's has zigzag customers support, and VirtueMart is no exception. On VirtueMart "Contact" pages clearly, stipulate that their form is strictly for the business partner purpose and not support. The best place you can get customer support is on their community forum or use their ticketing systems to submit your issues. Other support materials include VirtueMart Documentation and Tutorials. You can also try your luck on their Facebook and Twitter pages.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;The bottom line&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even though VirtueMart has its limitations, it is an easy and free way to convert your Joomla website into an eCommerce store. The plugin comes with many out-of-the-box features that help you sell your products online efficiently.&lt;br&gt;
I would recommend VirtueMart to all Joomla users that want to start selling their products online in the short run. If you have the financial investment and want a complete eCommerce platform solution that comes with everything needed for an eCommerce business and don't want to rely on third-party extensions, then there are better platforms available in the market like Shopping Cart Elite, BigCommerce, Volusion, etc.&lt;/p&gt;


</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/VirtueMart-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Ubercart Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in creating your online store using Drupal content management system (CMS) or convert your Drupal website into an eCommerce site? Then continue reading as we review Ubercart as modules for your Drupal CMS eCommerce solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ubercart is free to download and install open-source shopping cart plugin for Drupal based websites. Ubercart is a basic, easy to use add-on modules that offer eCommerce solutions and functionality to already existing websites. This allows you to upload products, apply attributes and sell them online. It's suitable for small to medium business that wants to sell their product online on a strict budget quickly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The modules itself is free of charge, but you will encounter some extra cost along the way to run an online store which includes domain names, SSL certificate, hosting and maintenance. You may also need to hire a developer to dig deep into the code to design a unique store for your online business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Setting up with Ubercart is a straightforward and easy process, allowing you to get your online store functioning fast without any little hassle. It is easy to use and configuring your store will not require any technical knowledge. However, your design options are limited with Ubercart, as there are no templates included and you will need a designer or programmer to change the theme files and CSS to your requirements.&lt;br&gt;
Ubercart is full of all the standard eCommerce features required to run an eCommerce business. This includes unlimited product and configurable product catalog, flexible product attributes, single page checkout &amp; anonymous checkout, simple order processing, order creation &amp; editing, XML import/export, order tracking, etc.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using Ubercart you might also consider adding the following essential modules to increase your eCommerce experience; Google Analytics, XML, Sitemaps, Newsletter and Emails, Related Products and Suggestions, Customer Reviews System, Affiliate System, Marketplace Setup, etc.&lt;br&gt;
Ubercart supports some of the popular payment systems which allow you to receive payment through PayPal, Payflow, Authorize.net, CyberSource, 2Checkout, PayTrace, USA ePay, Converge, etc.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ubercart large community of support and if you need help chances there is an answer in the community forum. Other support material includes documentations, Ubercart FAQ, user guides and the also provides a free demo to view the cart functionalities.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In conclusion, if you are looking for a quick way to sell product online using the Drupal CMS than Ubercart modules is your eCommerce solutions. It's a free module and open source which allows you to customize your website into a unique online store. Ubercart is incredibly flexible, reliable, and suitable for small to large businesses.&lt;br&gt;
I would recommend Ubercart to small businesses that are new to eCommerce with a low budget and product inventory. But if you are medium to large enterprise, there are better eCommerce platform in the market, which will deliver all in one eCommerce solution. If you are struggling to choose the right fit for your business, do not hesitate to contact us. We would be glad to offer you our professional services.
&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/Ubercart-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Shopsite Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;ShopSite is an award winning shopping cart which has been in the market for a long time. It has won its reputations as a trusted eCommerce Builder by many merchants of small to medium sized businesses.&lt;br&gt;
ShopSite is a cloud-based platform that lets you add eCommerce functionality to any website and instead of hosting your website, ShopSite outsource hosting to its affiliates. It's extremely basic and provides just enough features and tools to help you sell online. ShopSite enjoys positive reviews as one of the easiest to setup, manage and enjoyable to use.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Pricing&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ShopSite offers a free demo to test drive the platform before making any commitments; this allows the user to explore the cart functionality and features. The platform offers four pricing plans each has its benefits and limitations:

&lt;p&gt;1.Express Plan, which is free and includes features such as a 10 product limit (zero pages), mobile friendly checkout, add order buttons, WordPress plugin, secure/PCI certified;&lt;br&gt;
2.Starter Plan $5.99/month - includes features like a 15 product limit (5 pages), SEO friendly pages, mobile friendly, over 50 themes and 25 payment methods to choose from;&lt;br&gt;
3.Manager Plan $29.99/month - which includes the same features as Starter Plan, plus, unlimited product, unlimited pages, store search, real-time shipping rates, database and downloads;&lt;br&gt;
4.Pro Plan $59.99/month - which includes features as manager, plus coupons, quantity pricing, cross-selling, product reviews, Facebook store.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ease of Use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ShopSite has a natural user interface, in fact, the shopping cart has won awards as user-friendly and enjoyable to use. It is fast to setup, with their store wizard application you can be selling your products as soon as in 15 minutes.  The backend is intuitive and easy to navigate even a novice user will not have trouble using ShopSite panel.&lt;br&gt;
Many of ShopSite themes are responsive and depending on your HTML skills you can customize the templates as far as you can, which allow you to create a unique store for online business.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ShopSite offers all the necessary eCommerce feature solutions to start selling online, with many advanced features such as real-time shipping rates, discount coupons, a cross-selling and unlimited product available only on their Manager and Pro Plan.&lt;br&gt;
Some noticeable features that are available in the Manager and Pro Plan include advanced order options, search engine friendly HTML pages, data import wizard, product &amp; pages XML upload/download, easy order printing, Google analytics, mobile support, cart abandonment emails, HTML customer receipts, etc. You can view a full list on their website. There are several steps involved to start receiving payment. You will need to open a merchant account and payment gateway from the default providers and configure them in the backend by pressing 'commerce' then 'payment setup.' The platform is compatible with many payment gateways that include PayPal, Authorize.net, Google Wallet and Amazon Payments.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ShopSite customer support is outsourced to any third party hosting partners. If you are self-hosting your website, then you can purchase direct support from ShopSite.&lt;br&gt;
In additions to this ShopSite provide a knowledge base of resources, ShopSite forum, technical bulletin, documentations, video tutorials, support portal and general contact portal used for paid questions.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ShopSite is an excellent choice for those that are just getting started in the eCommerce business which offers simplicity and easy navigations. It does lack some professional features to take your business to the next level, but for the price, it's a good eCommerce starter program for small to medium business.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/Shopsite-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>PrestaShop Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;There are hundreds of eCommerce platform service providers in the eCommerce market, which makes it very lengthy process to choose the right platform for your eCommerce platform. This arises especially when choosing a free, open-source platform and paid hosting platform. When selecting a platform, we should remember that there is not the best platform as each offers a unique eCommerce experience and has their benefits and limitations. In today's article, we will review PrestaShop as your ideal eCommerce platform.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop overview&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrestaShop is among the most popular eCommerce platforms that allow business owners to sell their products /services completely free online. It's an open-source platform and offers you to either download the software and host it yourself or use PrestaShop's cloud-based alternative. Both open offer a wide list of out-of-the-box features and an easy-to-use admin panel.&lt;br&gt;
The platform is backed up with over 800 000 members who are always working to keep PrestaShop update and exclusively dedicated to open-source commerce.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop Pricing&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrestaShop is completely free to use, and there are no hidden fees for using this shopping cart. There are no transaction fees, and the platform offers a live demo to explore the admin and storefront on all devices. The cost of for PrestaShop setup is relatively small as they can be. If you use PrestaShop downloadable, then expect to pay for hosting, security and maintenance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop Cloud or Self-hosted&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Choosing between the cloud-based and self-hosted PrestaShop depends on some factors:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;PrestaShop Cloud&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instant store setup, free hosting and start selling quickly;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High speed hosting, subdomain and data storage are included;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customize default template or choose from hundreds of professional teams from PrestaShop add-ons;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rely on one-on-one assistance with the PrestaShop Support Plan and visits their forums;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must create a PrestaShop account and respect the terms and conditions of the shopping cart.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;PrestaShop self-hosted&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download PrestaShop, self-hosted and begin diving into the code;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose your hosting provider and manage your data backups;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit the code, install themes or upload your template;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure built-in modules, install modules from PrestaShop add-ons and upload your modules;
&lt;li&gt;Visit the forums for answers to technical questions or enjoy personal support with a PrestaShop Support plan;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Account creation is only required to participate in the forums and to make a purchase.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you choose PrestaShop downloadable, you have full control of the source code, and you can use non-PrestaShop modules and templates. When you choose PrestaShop cloud, you will get limited offerings, but you don't pay for hosting and benefits for an easier setup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop ease-to-use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ease to use and simplicity of your eCommerce experience will depend on which directions you choose. The cloud base is easy to setup and gets you running quickly, while self-hosted might require technical knowledge to configure but give you full access to source code for unique store customization.&lt;br&gt;
In general, the platform is flexible, scalable and easy to customize. PrestaShop offers over 2000 templates and 1800+ of them are responsive, allowing your website to be viewed on all devices. The admin panel allows you to flawlessly customize your online store without any hiccups and all the setting configuration a clearly displayed on the panel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrestaShop is feature-rich eCommerce solutions with over 300 features built-in the platform that every eCommerce business needs to run an online store successfully. This includes unlimited product listing, product quick view, attractive promotional banners, add-to-cart with cross-selling, instantly filtered search, intuitive interface, brilliant analytics tools, etc.&lt;br&gt;
Some marketing tools include coupons &amp; vouchers, customer reviews, set cart rules, email marketing, social sharing, advanced built-in SEO like customizable meta titles, meta descriptions, and URLs. Other noticeable features include +65 languages, multi-languages, tax calculations, flexible location-based logistics, etc.&lt;br&gt;
PrestaShop has 12 free pre-fabricated payment gateways which include PayPal, Authorize.net, BluePay Payments, Amazon Payments, First Data, Mercury Payment, etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an open-source platform like PrestaShop support can be very complicated, as programmers develop modules and templates. PrestaShop has a solid knowledge base resource which includes webinar, FAQ &amp; user guides, user forums, services from designers and developers, web ticketing, and paid support plans.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;PrestaShop bottom line&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PrestaShop is an ideal eCommerce solution, especially for small to medium business that wants to quickly sell online. The admin panel easy to use and give store owner full access to customize their online store in the baking. PrestaShop is filled with tons of out of the box features to run an online store and vast amount of add-ons to choose from.&lt;br&gt;
Top it off; PrestaShop is a free, open-source platform that is flexible, scalable and customizable as per requirement.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/PrestaShop-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>osCommerce Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;Selling goods and services through an online website is increasingly surpassing the traditional way of doing business. Many companies are changing their business strategies to accommodate the new market of selling online. The challenge that they encounter with this market is choosing the right platform to help them break through the virtual world. There are hundreds of thousands of eCommerce provider, each delivering their unique feature and services making the selection process tough.&lt;br&gt;
Today review article we are going to give an in-depth examination on osCommerce as your preferred eCommerce platform. Friendly reminder, each platform has their benefits and limitations.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OsCommerce is a simple and straightforward eCommerce platform that allows you to create and sell products online freely. It's an open-source shopping cart which is flexible and fully customizable to each user specific needs. However, its scalability is limited. OsCommerce is PHP base software that is downloadable to install on your server. It is mainly suitable for small to medium businesses, but large businesses are also welcome to osCommerce platform.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;OsCommerce Price&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;osCommerce is popular platform because it's a free and open-source eCommerce shopping cart, which allows the user to sell online freely. The only charges you should bear in mind are, hosting, security, domain name, and maintenance. At some point, you will also need a developer to dig deep into the source code to customize a unique online store for online business.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;osCommerce Ease-to-use&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;osCommerce is easy to use, easy to get running and easy to tweak the way you want it, but there are a few negative reviews on this point. When it comes to reliability and scalability and when your product reaches a certain size, your website might start cracking. The backend of the store is seemingly clean, but you should not expect something elegant and intuitive admin panel. Rather the admin panel is dated, but it does the job flawlessly. Most developers report struggling with several aspects of the shopping cart. However, we should know that each eCommerce platform has their pros and cons and osCommerce is not immune to this element.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;osCommerce Features&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After downloading and installing osCommerce; the shopping cart comes with essential eCommerce features for an eCommerce business website. This feature includes product catalog that offers an unlimited number of products, product categories, reviews, customer management, currency and language settings, tax handling, order processing, reports, some advanced tools like cache control, banner, database backups, security checks, etc.&lt;br&gt;
The plus side of using osCommerce, since it's an open-source platform you can quickly add 3rd party features you need. It also has an active community that helps better the platform. OsCommerce currently has over 7000 add-ons available for free to download on your website.
OsCommerce default payment gateways are PayPal, and it also integrates with various gateways such as SagePay, Dwolla, Amazon Checkout, etc. You can also expect to ship out your products with reliable shippers like FedEx, UPS, and USPS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;osCommerce Customer Support&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firstly, osCommerce has an active community forum with over 280 000 members that include developers, store owners and service providers to help you solve your daily issues using the platform. You can also get help using Live Chat with a community member. osCommerce documentations are also available where you will find all the information for setting up an osCommerce store&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;OsCommerce bottom line&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even though osCommerce has its shares of positive and negative reviews, you can create a good looking eCommerce website for free using their platform. It's an open-source eCommerce platform that allows you access to their source code which you can modify as per your requirements.
I will recommend osCommerce to business owners who want to test their viability to sell products online and small to medium business that do not have the financial means to use more advanced eCommerce platform.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/osCommerce-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Pinnacle Cart Reviews</title><description>	&lt;p&gt;When choosing an ideal eCommerce platform, we mostly prefer shopping cart that's easy to use and customizable to our needs. Pinnacle Cart is a popular hosted eCommerce platform that is easy to use and fully customizable. Pinnacle is an all-in-one eCommerce solution that capable of building an online store or help you sell on an existing website. This platform allows you a quickly add &amp; edit product, manage products and creates different promotional discount. It's a SaaS complaints platform, so you don't need to worry about hosting and website security.
