&lt;p&gt;Open source card has sloppy customer support as mostly they rely on community support. OpenCart advises users to try to search through their community forum before asking for support. They, however, have a good user forum, video tutorials, documentation, web ticket and blog.&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;In conclusion, OpenCart is an easy step by step shopping cart that allows you to freely sell your products online. They provide vast tutorial videos for setting up the platform, that even a novice will be able to figure out the system operations. if you have an in-house developer, you can easily scale and customize your website with tons of free templates.
If you are new to ecommerce, OpenCart is definitely your recommend ecommerce starting point solution.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/OpenCart-Review.aspx</link><pubDate>Sun, 02 Oct 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Demandware Reviews</title><description>&lt;p&gt;As we all know, choosing an eCommerce platform can be an overwhelming process that requires diligence study and time effort to get the perfect fit for your online business. In today in-depth reviews we are going to review Demandware as your eCommerce business solution.
Demandware is cloud-based and fully hosted eCommerce platform, which means you will not need to worry about security and maintenance cost. It uses a subscription base model that is based on the revenue sharing. This means the prices for hosting your website with Demandware will be based on the profit you make from your sales. This why Demandware personals are committed in offering their clients the best quality services and help them grow into a brand business. You can actually say that Demandware is worth every cent you pay as if they do not do a great job then there will be no income for both parties. So Demandware is your third-party business partner that, make sure that you generate income for your eCommerce business.
Demandware was on June 1, 2016, acquired by Salesforce, the #1 CRM to extend customers' success platform with the new Salesforce Commerce Cloud.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you don't have the technical knowledge than Demandware is your ideal business partners as the design, security, marketing and SEO optimization is included in the cost. This allows you to concentrate on more important matters of the business dealings. Demandware is mainly tailored for large sized, enterprise level business looking for an all-inclusive customized eCommerce solution.&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;Demandware is an Omni - channel platform that offers out-of-the-box features for eCommerce with POS and order management into one solution. They use an open architecture which makes building a unique with limitless customization and open API for easy integrations of features that you might be lacking in the DemandWare system. Although there are still technical SEO issues on dynamic page handling, Demandware offers friendly and flexible SEO system. Their control panel is seemly easy to use that it allows the user to manage multiple storefronts from a single back end. Demandware offers highly responsive web design that works flawlessly on the tablets and phones just as it work of desktops.
Other noticeable features of Demandware are; a lot of control over redirects, product management system with highly configurable product options, cross-sells &amp; up-sells, built-in PLP merchandising, customers segmentations, inventory management, and comprehensive email management system.&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;Demandware has a global team of technical support and development expert that provide 24/7 customers supports to customers and partners. They have a resource center and blog that they use to keep the community up to date with information on different topics. On top of this, Demandware offers services support from their partners; Link Technology Partners which offer value-added products and innovations that integrate and complement commerce cloud; Link Services Partners which help you amplify your brand and optimize your store ranking. LINK Services Partner Programs offer 3 unique partnership types: Solution, End-to-End, and Affiliate.
The bottom line, Demandware is all in one eCommerce solution, especially for large and enterprise level business. Demandware offers a unique LINK partner program that allows the customer to choose many value-added services that can improve their store.
In the eCommerce market, there is no "best eCommerce platform" as your choice is guided by the nature of your business, priorities and most important, your budget. You should go out there and explore the system, talk to their support team and find out what they are offering on the table and make your decision. Do not forget to ask for testing demos as that's the best way to see if a platform really delivers what they say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need more information on choosing the right eCommerce platform, feel free to contact us using the contact form on our blog.&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>http://www.ecommercespot.com/articles/Demandware-Reviews.aspx</link><pubDate>Wed, 28 Sep 2016 16:40:51 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Ecwid Review</title><description>&lt;p&gt;Ecwid is a hosted software solution for making an online store or allows you to sell a product online using your existing website. The platform is tailored for small to medium and enterprise business that have already a website and simply want to add an online store to it.
Ecwid is the easiest and cost-effective tool available in the eCommerce market that offers complete eCommerce solutions. Ecwid allows you to setup catalogs of products, add photos, pricing, weight for each product. The ability to define shipping rates, accept credit card payment has never been easy as using Ecwid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ecwid is the cheapest shopping cart in the market which offers a 4 pricing plan. Their free plan gives you an opportunity to try out their system plus also sell up to 10 products absolutely free, no transaction fees and an unlimited bandwidth. If the business is moving then you can move to their Venture Plan at a cost of $15 you can increase your product limits to 100 products. The 3rd plan is the Business Plan at a cost of $35, you get limits of 2500 product listing to your website and a whole new experience and more features. If you a large enterprise that holds tons of product range, than Ecwid got you covered. With the Unlimited plan, you free to add as many products as you need and all this for just $99 per month. As you can see, Ecwid perfect eCommerce partner, whether you are a small business that wants to try out the eCommerce market or large enterprise, Ecwid got you covered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of the advantages you will get from Ecwid is the flawless user interface. Ecwid is plug and play system, all you need to do is enter your email and password then you are ready to go. The admin panel clean and all the store settings and configuration options at right clearly visible.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ecwid has a few key features that every eCommerce business will go crazy about such as the responsive storefronts, that allows you website to display flawlessly across all devices - desktop, tablet or mobile. Their point-of-sale (POS) allows you to take payments on an IOS device. Another noticeable feature of Ecwid is language detection. Ecwid supports up to 45 different languages, so customers can view your store in their own language this is done automatically using the customer's browser settings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Ecwid features you can expect are; a variety of payment and shipping methods, easy checkout process, real-time shipping rates, store management that is equipped all product management tools, iOS and Android App for your store, level 1 PCI compliant, SEO, sell on multiple sites and smoothly integrates with WordPress, Joomla, Facebook, Tumblr, WIX, etc.
